# Modal dialogs and ESC

Any modal or dialog in the frontend (elements with `role="dialog"` and `aria-modal="true"`) **must** be dismissible when the user presses the **Escape** key.

## Implementation

- Attach a `keydown` handler to the dialog element (or a wrapper that has focus when the modal is open).
- In the handler, if `e.key === 'Escape'`, close the modal (e.g. set the open state to `false` or call the provided `onClose`/`onClosed` callback).
- Use `onkeydown` (or Svelte’s `onkeydown`) so the handler runs when the dialog (or its focusable content) has focus; if focus is managed on a container, ensure that container receives the key events.

## Example

```svelte
<div
  role="dialog"
  aria-modal="true"
  onkeydown={(e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Escape') onClose();
  }}
  tabindex="-1"
>
  <!-- dialog content -->
</div>
```

If the dialog is closed by other means (e.g. overlay click, Cancel button), use the same close logic for ESC so behavior is consistent.
